	<clause id="_solution_characterization" obligation="normative"><title>Solution characterization</title><clause id="matching" obligation="normative"><title>Matching modelled and measured values</title><p id="_63c2a43b-66ac-4f42-8624-4072b5cf7d9e">Let <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>I</mi></mstyle></math></stem> denote the set of indices of all radionuclides of concern and <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>L</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub></math></stem> the set of indices representing the laboratories that have measured radionuclide <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>i</mi></math></stem>.</p>
