	<clause id="measure_of_deviation" obligation="normative"><title>Measure of deviation of model from data</title><clause id="full_formulation" obligation="normative"><title>Full formulation</title><p id="_1ff34ee0-1e7e-4edf-9abd-28dca71287a3">If all the estimates <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>D</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></math></stem>, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>B</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></math></stem>, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>N</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></math></stem> and <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>R</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></math></stem> and their associated uncertainty matrices, discussed in <xref target="matching"/>, are to be used within the generalized non-linear least-squares regression, these estimates can be regarded as <em>prior</em> values of the corresponding quantities, and the results of the analysis would furnish <em>posterior</em> estimates of these quantities. In this context, denote by <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>Z</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></math></stem> the corresponding prior estimate of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>Z</mi></mstyle></mstyle></math></stem>,</p>
	<formula id="_8a3f425a-a4eb-46e7-9fa5-9b90b1fe5670" unnumbered="true">
	<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msup><mrow><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>Z</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mo>⊤</mo></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfenced open="[" close="]"><mrow><msup><mrow><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>B</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mo>⊤</mo></mrow></msup><mi>,</mi><msup><mrow><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>N</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mo>⊤</mo></mrow></msup><mi>,</mi><msup><mrow><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>R</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mo>⊤</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mi>,</mi></math></stem>
	</formula>
	<p id="_e2a37329-7b3a-492d-b866-2ed27b114d19">and by <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>V</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>Z</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mtext>diag</mtext><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>V</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>B</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></msub><mi>,</mi><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>V</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>N</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></msub><mi>,</mi><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>V</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>R</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></math></stem> the uncertainty matrix associated with <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mover accent="true"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mstyle mathvariant="bold"><mi>Z</mi></mstyle></mstyle></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></math></stem>.</p>
